Sure! Here's a simple JavaScript function that capitalizes the first letter of each word in a given string:

```javascript
function capitalizeFirstLetterOfEachWord(str) {
    return str.replace(/\b\w/g, char => char.toUpperCase());
}

// Example usage:
const input = "hello world";
const output = capitalizeFirstLetterOfEachWord(input);
console.log(output); // Outputs: "Hello World"
```

This function uses the `replace` method with a regular expression that matches the first character of each word (`\b\w`). It then converts that character to uppercase using an arrow function.
